About the year 1660, the flame of liberty occaſioned ſuch a conflux of people to Amſterdam, that the walls were extended, and by ſubſequent enlargements, they are become three leagues in circuit. The city is eſteemed nearly one third as populous as London or Paris; 
                  •
               nd within the walls are computed to be twenty-ſix thouſand five hundred houſes.
